the apartment is a 1960 american romantic comedy-drama film co-written produced and directed by billy wilder , and which stars jack lemmon , shirley maclaine , and fred macmurray .   it was wilder 's next movie after some like it hot and , like its predecessor , a commercial and critical success , grossing $ 25 million at the box office .   the film was nominated for ten academy awards , and won five , including best picture .   the film was the basis of the 1968 broadway musical promises , promises , with book by neil simon , music by burt bacharach , and lyrics by hal david .